<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-11-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-11-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="609" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d609">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Taylor</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-11-04"><hi rend="italic">November 4,
                                1896</hi></date>. (Received November 16.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 596.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your No. 595, of the 23d ultimo, containing further evidence
                            given by Mr. Wertheimer in his tobacco case, and to inform you that it
                            has been duly presented to the Spanish Government.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hannis Taylor</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>